• Fund Politicised — Jamoh Over $200 million contributed by indigenous ship owners operating in Nigeria may have been stuck in the Treasury Single Account (TSA) until the regulation guiding the disbursement is reviewed.  In his goodwill message, the Director-General of the Nigerian Maritime Administration and Safety Agency (NIMASA), Dr. Bashir Jamoh said that CVFF is politicised, but assured that the fund would be disbursed. 